# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [1.0.0] - 2026-03-18

Forked from [next-navigation-guard](https://github.com/LayerXcom/next-navigation-guard) v0.3.0
and published as `nextjs-nav-guard`.

### Added

- Centralized Next.js internal imports (`next/dist/*`) behind try/catch fallbacks for resilience
  across Next.js versions
- Local `AppRouterLike` type interface to avoid depending on Next.js internal type exports
- Dev-only console warning when `AppRouterContext` is unavailable (graceful degradation)
- Actionable error message with code example when `useNavigationGuard` is used without provider

### Fixed

- **Next.js 16.2 runtime crash** — added null guards on all `window.history.state` accesses
  in history augmentation, fixing `TypeError: Cannot read properties of null`
- **React rules-of-hooks violation** — fixed conditional `useContext` call in link click interceptor
- Removed dead code: unused `MutationObserver`, vestigial `needsInterceptor` ref,
  orphaned `_guardIntercepted` mutation
- Warn-once pattern for missing context warning (no console spam)

### Removed

- **Pages Router support** — removed `InterceptPagesRouterProvider`, `useInterceptedPagesRouter`,
  and all Pages Router code paths. App Router only.
- Self-referential dependency in package.json

### Changed

- Package renamed from `next-navigation-guard` to `nextjs-nav-guard`
- Debug log prefix changed to `[next-nav-guard]`
- DevDependencies updated to Next.js 16.2 and React 19

---

## Prior history (as `next-navigation-guard`)

### [0.3.0] - 2026-02-26

- Add `disableForTesting` option to `useNavigationGuard`
- Support Next.js 16 as peer dependency

### [0.2.0] - 2025-06-28

- Support for Next.js 15.3+ Link component
- Comprehensive E2E test suite using Playwright
- Support for React 19

### [0.1.2] - 2024-12-11

- Support Next.js 14 / 15 as peer dependencies

### [0.1.1] - 2024-10-07

- Fix back/forward button navigation

### [0.1.0] - 2024-09-18

- Initial release
